<item>
            <title>[STR-3070] Postback forms cause NPE with classic RequestProcessor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/STR-3070</link>
                <project id="12311043" key="STR">Struts 1</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I was unwittingly using the classic RequestProcessor when attempting to use postback forms. Unfortunately, I got a NPE:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java.lang.NullPointerException&lt;br/&gt;
	org.apache.struts.taglib.TagUtils.getActionMappingName(TagUtils.java:583)&lt;br/&gt;
	org.apache.struts.taglib.html.FormTag.lookup(FormTag.java:834)&lt;br/&gt;
	org.apache.struts.taglib.html.FormTag.doStartTag(FormTag.java:467)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I traced the problem back to a missing step in the classic RP. It does not set the ORIGINAL_URI key like the ComposableRequestProcessor. However, FormTag should explain this condition when a postback form is used but the key is absent.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
